{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52e9d4fd-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s2642"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2642"},"text":"§ 2642.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Analysis of imported merchandise","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Court of International Trade may order an analysis of imported merchandise and reports thereon by laboratories or agencies of the United States or laboratories accredited by the Customs Service under section 499(b) of the Tariff Act of 1930.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52e9d4fe-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/417/tIII/s301"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–417, title III, § 301","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-10"},"text":"Oct. 10, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1737"},"text":"94 Stat. 1737","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/182/tVI/s684/a/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–182, title VI, § 684(a)(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/2219"},"text":"107 Stat. 2219","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52e9d4ff-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id52e9d500-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id52e9d501-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 499(b) of the Tariff Act of 1930, referred to in text, is classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1499/b"},"text":"section 1499(b) of Title 19","children":[],"tail":", Customs Duties."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id52e9d502-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 2642, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-05-24/ch139/s123"},"text":"act May 24, 1949, ch. 139, § 123","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/106"},"text":"63 Stat. 106","children":[],"tail":", authorized the Customs Court under its rules and in its discretion to permit the amendment of protests, appeals and pleadings, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271/tI/s121"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–271, title I, § 121","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-06-02"},"text":"June 2, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/281"},"text":"84 Stat. 281","children":[],"tail":". See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s2633/b"},"text":"section 2633(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id52e9d503-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1993—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/182"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–182","children":[],"tail":" inserted before period at end “or laboratories accredited by the Customs Service under section 499(b) of the Tariff Act of 1930”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id52e9d504-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id52e9d505-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Application of 1993 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of applying amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/182"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–182","children":[],"tail":", any decision or order of Customs Service denying, suspending, or revoking accreditation of a private laboratory on or after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 1993","children":[],"tail":", and before regulations to implement "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1499/b"},"text":"19 U.S.C. 1499(b)","children":[],"tail":" are issued to be treated as having been denied, suspended, or revoked under such section 1499(b), see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/182/s684/b"},"text":"section 684(b) of Pub. L. 103–182","children":[],"tail":", formerly set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s1581"},"text":"section 1581 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id52e9d506-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of functions, personnel, assets, and liabilities of the United States Customs Service of the Department of the Treasury, including functions of the Secretary of the Treasury relating thereto, to the Secretary of Homeland Security, and for treatment of related references, see sections 203(1), 551(d), 552(d), and 557 of Title 6, Domestic Security, and the Department of Homeland Security Reorganization Plan of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"November 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", as modified, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s542"},"text":"section 542 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":". For establishment of U.S. Customs and Border Protection in the Department of Homeland Security, treated as if included in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/296"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–296","children":[],"tail":" as of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"Nov. 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s211"},"text":"section 211 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":", as amended generally by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/125"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–125","children":[],"tail":", and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/125/s802/b"},"text":"section 802(b) of Pub. L. 114–125","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s211"},"text":"section 211 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
